details.detail:
&lt;p&gt;Combine water, bay leaves, galangal, shiitaki mushrooms, bay leaves, and tiger lily blossoms in a large pot. Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fish out the tiger lily blossoms and bay leaves and discard. Puree the remaining mixture until smooth using an immersion blender. This is important because the galangal may give the soup a woody texture if not pureed!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add the corn starch slurry (see above) and other remaining ingredients (except rice noodles if using them) and simmer another 30 minutes. Meanwhile, lightly beat the eggs in a small bowl. Bring the soup to a rolling boil and drop the eggs into the boiling liquid. Reduce to a simmer and serve immediately.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you are using rice noodles, prepare them separately according to the instructions and add to individual bowls before serving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
